        "text": "After Hegel had only seen a way out by renewing a so to speak revolution-free primate of political ethics in the concept of the state beyond all the construction problems of the political system of bourgeois society, and Marx could only counter this with the absolutization of a social system conceived in purely economic terms, it has become necessary to re-found social theory. The marxistically conserved remnants offer little inspiration for this, but do make minimum demands on the breadth of vision and capacity for reflection that should not be undercut."
      },
