    {
      "type": "add",
      "id": "aebace6195be7365",
      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "aebace6195be7365",
        "text": "The following aspects must be taken up and combined if one is to attach any importance at all to connecting with previous thinking about society: (1) the traditional problem of the unity of the social system, which as a comprehensive system is at the same time only one social system among others, and (2) the modern (bourgeois) version of this problem as the necessity of self-selection of the social system, which implies (a) reflexivity of self-determination as a condition of the possibility of change of those subsystems, which assume a pars pro toto function by realizing a functional primacy, and (b) requires a temporalization of complexity in the precise sense that by incorporating \"historical consciousness\" into the social structure, indeterminacy of possibilities and determinacy of realizations become compatible in succession."
      },
